I"!J<h1 id="vicharanashala-lab-for-education-design">Vicharanashala Lab for Education Design</h1>

<h2 id="nptel-winter-internship--frequently-asked-questions">NPTEL Winter Internship – Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<hr />

<h2 id="1-dates--duration">1. Dates &amp; Duration</h2>

<h3 id="11-what-is-the-start-and-end-date-of-this-internship">1.1 What is the start and end date of this internship?</h3>

<p>This winter internship is hosted by the Indian Institute of Technology Ropar in online mode and will begin on <strong>December 22nd</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="12-what-is-the-duration-of-this-internship">1.2 What is the duration of this internship?</h3>

<p>The internship is hosted at the Indian Institute of Technology Ropar in <strong>online mode</strong> and will be of <strong>4 weeks</strong> duration.</p>

<h3 id="13-what-is-the-mode-of-this-internship">1.3 What is the mode of this internship?</h3>

<p>The internship mode will be <strong>online only</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="14-what-are-the-timings-and-schedule-of-this-internship">1.4 What are the timings and schedule of this internship?</h3>

<p>Internship hours are scheduled between <strong>9:00 AM and 6:00 PM</strong>, from <strong>Monday to Saturday</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="2-mode-of-internship--attendance">2. Mode of Internship &amp; Attendance</h2>

<h3 id="21-can-we-opt-for-an-on-campusoffline-internship">2.1 Can we opt for an on-campus/offline internship?</h3>

<p>We appreciate the interest in an offline internship, but the program will be conducted in <strong>online mode</strong>, which is designed to ensure an equivalent learning experience.</p>

<h3 id="22-is-my-attendance-at-online-sessions-compulsory">2.2 Is my attendance at online sessions compulsory?</h3>

<p>Yes, attendance at every online session is <strong>mandatory</strong>.</p>

<p>You may receive up to <strong>two warnings</strong> for non-compliance. Further violations may result in the <strong>loss of your internship opportunity</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="23-i-registered-using-one-name-but-attend-sessions-with-a-different-name-or-email-will-this-affect-my-attendance">2.3 I registered using one name but attend sessions with a different name or email. Will this affect my attendance?</h3>

<p>Yes. Please attend using the <strong>same name and email ID</strong> that you used during registration with NPTEL.</p>

<p>Failure to do so may result in your attendance <strong>not being recorded</strong>, and repeated violations may <strong>disqualify you</strong> from continuing.</p>

<h3 id="24-should-i-fill-the-attendance-sheet-attached-to-the-offer-letter-given-by-nptel">2.4 Should I fill the attendance sheet attached to the offer letter given by NPTEL?</h3>

<p>If you received an attendance sheet from NPTEL, please <strong>clarify this directly with the NPTEL team</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="3-mentorship--guidance">3. Mentorship &amp; Guidance</h2>

<h3 id="31-will-the-course-instructor-supervise-our-work-directly">3.1 Will the course instructor supervise our work directly?</h3>

<p>The course instructor <strong>may interact</strong> with interns during the internship, depending on the nature of the project.</p>

<p>Mentors and coordinators will interact with interns via <strong>live sessions</strong> and <strong>discussion forums</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="4-support-and-resolution-protocol">4. Support and Resolution Protocol</h2>

<h3 id="41-where-do-i-raise-my-concern-initially">4.1 Where do I raise my concern initially?</h3>

<p>Please follow this process:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Send an email to <strong>internship-support@vicharanashala.zohodesk.in</strong>.</li>
  <li>Our support team will respond <strong>within 2 hours</strong> of your submission between <strong>9:00 AM and 9:00 PM</strong>.</li>
  <li>Any question submitted after <strong>9:00 PM</strong> will be answered on the <strong>next day</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="42-what-if-i-dont-receive-a-response-within-24-hours">4.2 What if I don’t receive a response within 24 hours?</h3>

<p>If you do not receive a response within <strong>24 hours</strong>, you may raise a <strong>second ticket</strong>.</p>

<p>In the subject line, mention:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>“Attention Please – Follow-up on Ticket #[Original Ticket Number]”</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>This ticket will be escalated to our <strong>Mentors Team</strong>, who will reach out to you for a <strong>voice call discussion</strong> and try to resolve the issue directly.</p>

<h3 id="43-who-will-respond-to-my-second-ticket">4.3 Who will respond to my second ticket?</h3>

<p>The <strong>Mentors Team</strong> will handle the second ticket and schedule a <strong>voice call</strong> to ensure your issue is clearly understood and resolved.</p>

<h3 id="44-if-my-concern-still-isnt-addressed-how-do-i-escalate-further">4.4 If my concern still isn’t addressed, how do I escalate further?</h3>

<p>After <strong>48 hours</strong> of your first ticket (and after raising a follow-up ticket), you can escalate the matter via email to the <strong>Internship Sponsor</strong>, with CC to <strong>Prof. Sudarshan Iyengar</strong>, and the following recipients in CC:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Your department’s <strong>faculty reference</strong></li>
  <li>Your department <strong>HOD</strong></li>
  <li>The <strong>DLED Team</strong> at <strong>dled@iitrpr.ac.in</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>Ensure that your email includes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Your <strong>full name</strong> and <strong>department</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Reference numbers</strong> and <strong>dates</strong> of the two Zoho Desk tickets</li>
  <li>A <strong>brief explanation</strong> of the unresolved issue</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="45-why-do-i-need-to-include-my-faculty-reference-and-hod-in-the-final-escalation-email">4.5 Why do I need to include my faculty reference and HOD in the final escalation email?</h3>

<p>This ensures <strong>transparency</strong> and allows your academic mentors to support you while helping us maintain <strong>accountability</strong> and <strong>timely resolution</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="46-is-this-process-mandatory-for-all-issues">4.6 Is this process mandatory for all issues?</h3>

<p>Yes. To maintain consistency and ensure efficient support, we request all interns to follow this <strong>three-step resolution path</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="5-stipend-and-certification">5. Stipend and Certification</h2>

<h3 id="51-where-can-i-find-information-on-stipend-and-certification">5.1 Where can I find information on stipend and certification?</h3>

<p>For all <strong>stipend</strong> and <strong>certification</strong> queries or concerns, please refer to the <strong>official NPTEL website</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="52-will-the-course-instructor-provide-recommendation-letters-after-the-internship">5.2 Will the course instructor provide recommendation letters after the internship?</h3>

<p>Recommendation letters are <strong>not guaranteed</strong>.</p>

<p>You may request one from the course instructor after <strong>successfully completing the internship</strong>, and it will be at their <strong>discretion</strong>, based on your performance.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="6-completion--certification">6. Completion &amp; Certification</h2>

<h3 id="61-what-are-the-internship-completion-criteria">6.1 What are the internship completion criteria?</h3>

<p>To successfully complete the internship, the following criteria must be met:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Attendance</strong>: 100% attendance (with <strong>1 day of eligible leave</strong> allowed)</li>
  <li><strong>Course</strong>: Completion of the <strong>MERN development course</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Project Completion</strong>: Each student must complete the <strong>assigned project</strong> under the guidance of a <strong>mentor</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>These criteria will be <strong>strictly monitored</strong> throughout the internship period.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="7-report-submission--deadline">7. Report Submission &amp; Deadline</h2>

<p>Please ensure all submissions fall within the <strong>Timely Submission Category</strong> to avoid being <strong>flagged as a defaulter</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="8-termination--rejoining">8. Termination &amp; Rejoining</h2>

<h3 id="81-i-received-a-termination-email-due-to-overlapping-academic-commitments-but-my-exams-are-over-now-can-i-rejoin-the-current-internship-batch">8.1 I received a termination email due to overlapping academic commitments, but my exams are over now. Can I rejoin the current internship batch?</h3>

<p>No. The internship is a <strong>full-time commitment</strong>, and any <strong>academic overlap</strong>, even if temporary, disqualifies a participant from continuing.</p>

<p>You will need to <strong>apply again</strong> for the <strong>next available internship batch</strong> if interested.</p>

<h3 id="82-can-i-appeal-my-termination-if-i-have-valid-reasons-for-missing-assignments-or-sessions">8.2 Can I appeal my termination if I have valid reasons for missing assignments or sessions?</h3>

<p>The internship policy allows <strong>no leniency</strong>.</p>

<p>If you have already received an official termination notice due to <strong>lack of attendance</strong>, <strong>late submissions</strong>, or <strong>academic overlap</strong>, your internship <strong>cannot be reinstated</strong>.</p>

<p>These rules are strict to maintain <strong>fairness</strong> and <strong>program quality</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="83-i-plan-to-rejoin-the-internship-later-will-it-be-the-same-program">8.3 I plan to rejoin the internship later. Will it be the same program?</h3>

<p>If you wish to participate again, you must <strong>reapply</strong> and go through the <strong>selection process</strong> for the next batch.</p>

<p>Please note that <strong>future internships may not be funded</strong> by any organization or <strong>IIT Ropar</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="9-vibe">9. ViBe</h2>

<h3 id="91-how-do-i-log-in-to-the-vibe-platform">9.1 How do I log in to the ViBe platform?</h3>

<p>Follow these steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Use the <strong>invite link</strong> sent to your registered email. You will receive an email from <strong>Vicharanashala</strong>.</li>
  <li>Open the email and click the <strong>“Accept Invite”</strong> button.</li>
  <li>You will be redirected to the <strong>ViBe</strong> page.</li>
  <li>Click on <strong>“Continue as Student”</strong>. Always log in as a <strong>Student</strong>.</li>
  <li>After clicking “Continue as Student”, you will be redirected to the next page.</li>
  <li>Click on <strong>“Continue with Google”</strong> and sign in using your <strong>registered email ID</strong> (the one where you received the invite link).</li>
  <li>You will then be redirected to the <strong>Dashboard</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="92-i-accepted-the-invite-but-it-shows-no-course-enrolled-what-should-i-do">9.2 I accepted the invite, but it shows “No course enrolled.” What should I do?</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the <strong>Profile</strong> section of your dashboard.</li>
  <li>Make sure you are signed in with the <strong>same email ID</strong> you used during registration. You can verify this by logging into the Google account where you originally received the registration link.</li>
  <li>If your institute uses an <strong>alias email</strong>, try logging in with the <strong>registered ID directly</strong>.</li>
  <li>If the issue persists, inform <strong>Support</strong>, so they can <strong>manually add you</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="93-videos-are-not-playing--stuck-on-repeat">9.3 Videos are not playing / stuck on repeat.</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Make sure you are watching the videos in <strong>sequential order</strong> without skipping.</li>
  <li>Allow <strong>camera</strong> and <strong>microphone</strong> access (mandatory for progress tracking).</li>
  <li>Clear your browser <strong>cache and cookies</strong>, then refresh with <strong>Ctrl + Shift + R</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="94-i-am-getting-an-access-restricted-error">9.4 I am getting an “Access Restricted” error.</h3>

<p>This usually happens if a <strong>step is skipped</strong>.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Please watch each video <strong>in order</strong>.</li>
  <li>If the issue persists, try refreshing the page by pressing <strong>Ctrl + R</strong>. You may be redirected to the <strong>dashboard</strong>, but you can return to your course and continue from where you left off.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="95-my-quiz-answers-are-correct-but-the-system-is-marking-them-wrong">9.5 My quiz answers are correct, but the system is marking them wrong.</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Note the <strong>video number</strong> and <strong>case study name</strong>.</li>
  <li>Report the issue to the <strong>Support Desk</strong>.</li>
  <li>In some cases, the issue is resolved from the <strong>backend within a few hours</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="96-my-dashboard-shows-less-than-100-even-after-completing-all-videosquizzes">9.6 My dashboard shows less than 100% even after completing all videos/quizzes.</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Sometimes, progress may take <strong>time to update</strong>.</li>
  <li>Refresh your browser and check again.</li>
  <li>In case of discrepancies, the <strong>Google Sheet records</strong> maintained by organizers are considered <strong>final</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="97-i-cannot-find-my-course-on-the-dashboard">9.7 I cannot find my course on the dashboard.</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Accept the <strong>invite link</strong> from your registered email.</li>
  <li>If you already accepted, check under <strong>“Invites”</strong> (top-right of the dashboard).</li>
  <li>Accept the course invite by clicking the <strong>“Invites”</strong> button at the top-right corner of the page.</li>
  <li>If you’re still unable to view your courses on the dashboard, please reach out to the <strong>Support Desk</strong> for assistance.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="98-how-do-i-get-my-certificate">9.8 How do I get my certificate?</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Certificates are issued only if <strong>all requirements</strong> are completed (100% videos, quizzes, assignments, polls, and project components, if applicable).</li>
  <li>Certificates are compiled after <strong>verification</strong>.</li>
  <li>They will then be sent to your <strong>registered email</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="99-i-missed-completing-the-course-within-the-deadline-what-should-i-do">9.9 I missed completing the course within the deadline. What should I do?</h3>

<p>If you could not finish before the <strong>deadline</strong>, you will need to <strong>register again</strong> for the <strong>next cohort</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h3 id="910-can-we-use-a-mobile-or-tablet-to-access-the-program">9.10 Can we use a mobile or tablet to access the program?</h3>

<p>No. The software <strong>cannot be accessed</strong> using a mobile phone or tablet.</p>

<p>Please ensure you are using a <strong>desktop, PC, or laptop</strong> with an active <strong>camera</strong> and <strong>microphone</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h3 id="911-what-is-the-last-date-for-completion-of-all-vibe-activity">9.11 What is the last date for completion of all ViBe activity?</h3>

<p>All <strong>ViBe-related activities and assignments</strong> must be completed by the <strong>deadline mentioned in your welcome email</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<h3 id="912-vibe-is-not-detecting-my-face-what-should-i-do">9.12 ViBe is not detecting my face. What should I do?</h3>

<p>To ensure your face is properly detected by the software, please follow these guidelines:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Sit in a <strong>well-lit room</strong>.</li>
  <li>Keep your <strong>face uncovered</strong> at all times.</li>
  <li>Ensure the <strong>background is clear</strong> and not blurred.</li>
  <li>Position the camera so that it captures your <strong>entire face</strong>.</li>
  <li>Avoid lighting that causes <strong>glare or shadow</strong> on your face.</li>
  <li>Confirm that your <strong>camera is switched on</strong> and has the necessary <strong>permissions</strong>.</li>
  <li>Sit in a <strong>quiet place</strong> to avoid disturbances.</li>
  <li>Ensure <strong>no one else</strong> is visible in the camera frame.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="913-why-cant-i-log-in-or-access-vibe">9.13 Why can’t I log in or access ViBe?</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Ensure that you have <strong>accepted the invite link</strong> sent to your registered email ID.</li>
  <li>If it still doesn’t work, refresh the page by pressing <strong>Ctrl + R</strong> or clear the cache by pressing <strong>Ctrl + Shift + R</strong>.</li>
  <li>If the issue persists, contact our <strong>Support Desk</strong> via email or message, providing:
    <ul>
      <li>Your <strong>name</strong></li>
      <li>Your <strong>registered email ID</strong></li>
      <li>A <strong>screenshot or screen recording</strong> of the problem</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="914-why-do-i-see-the-quiz-failed-option-every-time-i-submit-my-answers">9.14 Why do I see the “Quiz Failed” option every time I submit my answers?</h3>

<p>This issue can occur for several reasons. You can try the following steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Refresh the page using <strong>Ctrl + R</strong>.</li>
  <li>Log out and <strong>log in again</strong>.</li>
  <li>If you still face the same issue, contact the <strong>Support Desk</strong> via email or message, providing your <strong>name</strong>, <strong>registered email ID</strong>, and a <strong>screenshot or screen recording</strong> of the problem.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h3 id="915-why-do-my-videos-auto-restart">9.15 Why do my videos auto-restart?</h3>

<p>Videos may auto-restart due to the following reasons:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Face not detected</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong>Blurred background</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong>Background noise</strong> being detected.</li>
  <li>Face is <strong>not clearly visible</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong>More than one person</strong> is detected in the camera frame.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h2 id="10-github-assignment-submission">10. GitHub Assignment Submission</h2>

<h3 id="101-how-do-i-submit-my-github-assignment">10.1 How do I submit my GitHub assignment?</h3>

<p>Follow these steps to submit your GitHub assignments (video demonstration: <a href="https://youtu.be/lrpjRo9Z02Y">https://youtu.be/lrpjRo9Z02Y</a>):</p>

<ol>
  <li>Click the <strong>assignment link</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong>Sign in with GitHub</strong>.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>“Accept assignment”</strong>.</li>
  <li>Your <strong>personal repository</strong> will be created.</li>
  <li>Open the files <strong><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">namasthey.js</code></strong> and <strong><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">loops.js</code></strong>.</li>
  <li>Write your <strong>code</strong>.</li>
  <li><strong>Commit and push</strong> your changes.</li>
</ol>

